## What

Part of #401 (item 2: typing → framework heartbeat adapter).

Consolidates the scattered `typingCallbacks.onCleanup?.()` calls into a single outer `finally` block, ensuring typing indicator stops reliably on **all** exit paths:
- ✅ Success (final reply delivered)
- ✅ Error (LLM failure, network, etc.)
- ✅ Abort (superseded by newer message in same channel)
- ✅ Unexpected early return

### Before
Cleanup was called in 3 separate locations — easy to miss a path.

### After
- `deliver()` calls cleanup early (typing stops before final message appears — required for existing test behavior)
- Outer `finally` is the idempotent safety net covering all exits

## Tests
All 111 tests pass (63 behavioral tests in `dispatch-behavior.test.ts` included). No behavior change — structural cleanup only.

Refs: #401
